A Lotus Park resident was shot thrice and robbed of his cash after he was allegedly followed from the bank by four suspects to his home in Isipingo, a short while ago. According to a local resident, the Thrush Place victim was allegedly followed from the bank after withdrawing an unknown amount of cash. “The victim was accosted on his driveway and shot three times on his upper body. The suspects allegedly came in a white Ford Figo and made off with the cash. The victim was rushed to hospital privately,” said the resident. According to additional information received via WhatsApp crime groups, the suspects wore balaclavas and fled in a white Ford Fiesta. The scene is still active and all relevant authorities are in attendance. The condition of the victim is unknown at this stage.